Here is the fix and instructions.

h2. Description

{excerpt}The Confluence Documentation Theme is a newer Confluence theme that is designed to facilitate wikis used for documentation.{excerpt} 

h2. Version 1.0.4

Documentation Theme 1.0.4 is the newest version that is compatible with Confluence 3.1.2 (what is currently deployed the production wiki server).  


This theme does not render well on the BlackBerry 6 browser.  This is due to the theme's use of scrollable divs to implement the navigation splitter.  

The theme doesn't have this problem on iPod touch or iPhone devices.  This is because the theme uses a bit of Javascript to disable the splitter on those devices.

{code:lang=javascript|title=doctheme/doc-theme.js}
// Don't display the sidebard on the iPhone. Will need to support other phones in the future.
if((navigator.userAgent.match(/iPhone/i)) || (navigator.userAgent.match(/iPod/i))) {
    AJS.$("#splitter-sidebar").hide();
}
else {
...
{code}

The simple fix is to expand this to check for BlackBerry browsers.

{code:lang=javascript|title=doctheme/doc-theme.js}
// Don't display the sidebard on the iPhone. Will need to support other phones in the future.
if((navigator.userAgent.match(/iPhone/i))
|| (navigator.userAgent.match(/iPod/i))
|| (navigator.userAgent.match(/BlackBerry 9800/i))
|| (navigator.userAgent.match(/BlackBerry 9780/i))) {
    AJS.$("#splitter-sidebar").hide();
}
else {
...
{code}

I'm not sure if it would be sufficient to just check for BlackBerry.  I suppose that if the newer WebKit browsers have problems with the splitter, then older devices will too.  I don't have a pre-6.0 device handy to test with, so I just put in checks for the devices that I do have.

A patched version of the theme is also attached: [^doctheme-1.0.4-rim.jar]

This patch isn't perfect by any measure.  It doesn't check for other 6.0 devices. It doesn't handle pre-6.0 devices. It doesn't handle PlayBook.  And although the sidebar is hidden, it looks like the space is still reserved so the content doesn't flow to fill the width of the screen.  But even with these limitations, it's still a lot better than the stock version.

