Raising this improvement request on behalf of [CSP-57803|https://support.atlassian.com/browse/CSP-57803] (restricted to public):

These are the files/directories that consist of space character:
{noformat}
halatas@halatas-laptop:~/src/install_dir/confluence-3.4.9-std$ find . -type f -name *' '*
./bin/OS X - Run Confluence In Terminal Window.command
./bin/OS X - Run Confluence In Background.command
./bin/OS X - Stop Confluence.command
halatas@halatas-laptop:~/src/install_dir/confluence-3.4.9-std$ find . -type d -name *' '*
./confluence/images/ddtree/black spinner
{noformat}

Here is one of the reason (use case) of this improvement request:
{quote}
As we package confluence with RPM to deploy it and keep track of changes, we noticed that a few files contain blanks, which shouldn't be necassary:

bin/OS X - *
confluence/images/ddtree/black spinner/*.png

Of course it isn't your fault that rpmbuild has problems to handle such filenames, but while I could simply remove the "OS X" stuff, I cannot remove the black spinner files, because they surely are used somwhere within the wiki. Could you please rename it to "black-spinner", "black_spinner" or something similar?
{quote}

{quote}
the best reason for you is to be consistent with all other dirs and filenames. While the "OS X" stuff is not of interest for me, "black 
spinner" is the only occurence of a blank in a file name or dir name in the whole confluence code. In all other cases you renamed it to a dash \(-). The PNGs in the black spinner dir are ment to be used by the confluence wiki by web, but " " is not a valid URL in a browser. It must be converted. So another point to rename it as in all other cases.

No, the only files where something from the "black spinner" dir is referenced is in confluence/includes/js/ddtree/spinner.js and spinner-min.js, so it can be easily changed.

So all your developers had to do was a rename of the "black spinner" directory and a replace of all "black spinner" occurences in both files to "black-spinner". That's a one-off action of less than 10 minutes.
{quote}

