I've noticed that when customers give us thread dumps of slow-running indexing, about half the threads are usually stuck in:

{noformat}
com.atlassian.confluence.search.lucene.extractor.ContentEntityMetadataExtractor#extractCreatorAndModifier
{noformat}

Specifically the part where it gets the full history of the content entity so that it can extract the set of usernames of people who've worked on the content.  It would seem more efficient to just get that list of users directly from the DB.

Since the version histories are cached, there's some chance that the version histories will be looked up by something else in the indexing, but otherwise I think it should be a decent speed-up.

